The abducted Baale (traditional ruler) of Araromi village, Chief Tafa Apanpa, and his wife have regained freedom from kidnappers It was learnt that the couple were released on Thursday night but the amount paid as ransom to secure their release was not revealed. Oyo state on the map
SaharaReporters Media However, Ido local government council chairman, Sheriff Adeojo visited the community on Thursday and assured the residents of the community that the monarch would soon be released. Apanpa and his wife were kidnapped in his house at Araromi in the Ido Local Government Area of the state on Tuesday night by unknown gunmen.